==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Aversation
<hw>Av`er*sa"tion</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>aversatio</ets>, fr. <ets>aversari</ets> to turn away, v. intens.
of <ets>avertere</ets>. See <er>Avert</er>.]</ety> <def>A turning from
with dislike; aversion.</def> <mark>[Obs.or Archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Some men have a natural <qex>aversation</qex> to some vices or
virtues, and a natural affection to others.</q> <rj><qau>Jer.
Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Averse</ent>⟦br⟧
